[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     19[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     20[0m:[38;5;10m[49m For this example, we'll build the entire pipeline locally with synthetic data. The SageMaker integration points are noted where you'd swap in real endpoint calls.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     21[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     22[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ---
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     23[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     24[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ## Config and Constants
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     25[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     26[0m:[38;5;10m[49m These thresholds and parameters control the intervention timing logic. In production, these would be tuned based on clinical validation studies and care team feedback. Start conservative (higher thresholds, longer cooldown periods) and loosen as you build confidence in the model's calibration.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     27[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     28[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```python
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     29[0m:[38;5;10m[49m import logging
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     30[0m:[38;5;10m[49m from decimal import Decimal
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     31[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     32[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # Structured logging. Never log PHI field values (patient names, MRNs, etc.).
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     33[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # Log patient_id only when necessary for debugging, and ensure logs are
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     34[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # stored in HIPAA-compliant destinations with appropriate access controls.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     35[0m:[38;5;10m[49m logger = logging.getLogger(__name__)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     36[0m:[38;5;10m[49m logger.setLevel(logging.INFO)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     37[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     38[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # --- Hazard thresholds ---
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     39[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # These define what "high risk" and "moderate risk" mean in terms of daily hazard.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     40[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # A daily hazard of 0.05 means roughly a 5% chance of the target event on that day,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     41[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # given the patient has survived to that day.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     42[0m:[38;5;10m[49m HIGH_RISK_THRESHOLD = 0.05
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     43[0m:[38;5;10m[49m MODERATE_RISK_THRESHOLD = 0.02
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     44[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     45[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # --- Intervention scoring thresholds ---
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     46[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # These control when the system recommends action vs. continued monitoring.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     47[0m:[38;5;10m[49m URGENT_THRESHOLD = 80.0       # Score above this = "intervene today or tomorrow"
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     48[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ACTION_THRESHOLD = 40.0       # Score above this = "intervene this week"
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     49[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     50[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # --- Intervention fatigue parameters ---
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     51[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # Minimum days between outreach attempts to avoid patient fatigue.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     52[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # Calling a patient every 3 days trains them to ignore you.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     53[0m:[38;5;10m[49m MIN_INTERVENTION_GAP_DAYS = 14
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     54[0m:[38;5;10m[49m FATIGUE_DAMPENING = 0.3       # Multiply score by this if within cooldown period
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     55[0m:[38;5;10m[49m DECLINED_DAMPENING = 0.1      # Multiply score by this if patient recently declined
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     56[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     57[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # --- Model parameters ---
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     58[0m:[38;5;10m[49m FORECAST_HORIZON_DAYS = 30    # How many days ahead the model predicts
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     59[0m:[38;5;10m[49m LOOKBACK_DAYS = 730           # How far back to look for patient history (2 years)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     60[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
